def: A tropical tree, or its fruit, of the genus Psidium. Twovarieties are well known, the P. pyriferum, or white guava, and P.pomiferum, or red guava. The fruit or berry is shaped like apomegranate, but is much smaller. It is somewhat astringent, butmakes a delicious jelly.
Want of love to mankind; -- the opposite of philanthropy. Coxe.
A vessel for water for washing the hands; also, one to holdwine or water.
An instrument which registers meteorologic phases orconditions.
The quality of being compressible; compressibility.
One of two magistrates of Rome who took a register of thenumber and property of citizens, and who also exercised the office ofinspector of morals and conduct.
Formed like, or resembling, a honeycomb.
Blood formative; -- applied to a substance in early fetal life,which breaks up gradually into blood vessels.
A large squirrel fish (Holocentrus ascensionis) of Florida andthe West Indies.
Striving to excel; ambitious; emulous. [Obs.] "A most emulatepride." Shak.
Doubly serrate, or having the serratures serrate, as in someleaves.
